      <div class="prose">
        <p>Hidden costs matter for both platforms. Workiz charges $29/month for QuickBooks integration and $19/month for advanced reporting. Jobber includes most integrations but charges $49/month for advanced inventory management and $39/month for the customer portal.</p>
        
        <p>For a 8-person HVAC team, total annual costs typically run $5,880 for Workiz versus $4,728 for Jobber, making Jobber 20% more cost-effective at this size.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="background: #e3f2fd; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600;">Ready to try Jobber for your HVAC business?</p>
        <p style="margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">Get started with a 14-day free trial and see why 200,000+ service businesses choose Jobber.</p>
        <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow" style="display: inline-block; background: #2563eb; color: white; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600;">Start Free Trial</a>
      </div>

      <h2 id="core-features">Core Features Comparison</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Scheduling capabilities differ significantly between platforms. Workiz offers drag-and-drop scheduling with resource management, technician skill matching, and route optimization for teams over 15 techs. Color coding supports 12 job types with custom statuses.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber's scheduling focuses on simplicity with calendar views, automatic scheduling suggestions, and GPS tracking. The system handles recurring maintenance contracts well but lacks advanced resource allocation features larger teams need.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Invoicing and Estimates</h3>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Workiz provides detailed estimate templates with line-item pricing, material markups, and approval workflows. The system generates estimates 23% faster than manual methods but requires initial template setup. Custom fields support complex commercial pricing structures.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber's estimate-to-invoice conversion happens in 2 clicks versus Workiz's 4-step process. Templates cover standard residential HVAC work, with automatic tax calculations and payment processing through Stripe or Square integration.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Customer Communication</h3>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Both platforms send automatic appointment reminders, but execution differs. Workiz supports SMS, email, and voice calls with 94% delivery rates. Customization allows branded templates and multi-language support for diverse markets.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber's communication feels more personal with tech photos, real-time arrival notifications, and customer feedback collection. The customer portal allows easy rebooking and service history access, reducing office calls by 35%.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="mobile-experience">Mobile Experience</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Mobile performance creates the biggest user experience gap between these platforms. Jobber's mobile app receives 4.7/5 star ratings across app stores, with technicians completing job updates 40% faster than desktop alternatives.</p>
        
        <p>Workiz mobile functionality covers core features but feels cramped on smaller screens. Complex forms require scrolling, and photo uploads occasionally fail on slower connections. However, offline capability works better than Jobber's limited offline mode.</p>
      </div>

