            <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Complex, requires scrolling</td>
            <td style="padding: 12px; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Streamlined, single page</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="integrations">Integrations & Add-ons</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Workiz integrates with 45+ third-party applications including QuickBooks, Salesforce, and specialized HVAC tools like Load Calc Pro. API access allows custom integrations for enterprise clients, though implementation requires technical expertise.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber offers 35+ integrations focused on small business needs. QuickBooks, Zapier, and Mailchimp connections work smoothly out of the box. The platform prioritizes plug-and-play functionality over extensive customization options.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Accounting Integration</h3>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Both platforms sync with QuickBooks Online, but data mapping differs. Workiz provides detailed GL account matching and handles complex job costing for commercial projects. The integration costs $29/month but includes real-time synchronization.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber's QuickBooks integration is free and covers standard invoicing, payments, and customer data. However, project-based accounting and detailed job costing require workarounds that complicate commercial HVAC operations.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="customer-support">Customer Support</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Support quality impacts daily operations significantly. Workiz provides phone support during business hours (8 AM - 6 PM EST) with average wait times of 4-7 minutes. Email responses typically arrive within 4 hours, though complex technical issues may take 24-48 hours to resolve.</p>
        
        <p>Jobber's support operates 6 AM - 8 PM local time across North American time zones. Live chat resolves 78% of issues immediately, with phone support averaging 2-minute wait times. The knowledge base contains 400+ articles covering common HVAC scenarios.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>Training resources favor Jobber significantly. Their HVAC-specific onboarding includes video tutorials, live webinars, and dedicated success managers for teams over 10 users. Workiz provides general training materials but lacks industry-specific guidance.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="verdict">Final Verdict</h2>
      
      <div class="prose">
        <p><strong>Choose Jobber if:</strong> Your HVAC team focuses on residential service calls, you have 2-15 technicians, you prioritize ease of use over customization, or you need faster team adoption. Jobber costs less and delivers better mobile experiences for straightforward operations.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Choose Workiz if:</strong> You handle complex commercial HVAC projects, manage 15+ technicians, need extensive customization, or require detailed project management features. The higher cost and complexity pay off for sophisticated operations.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="background: #f0f9ff; padding: 1.5rem; border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
        <h4 style="margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; color: #1e40af;">Our Recommendation</h4>
        <p style="margin: 0;">For most HVAC contractors, Jobber provides better value through faster implementation, superior mobile experience, and lower total costs. Consider Workiz only if you need complex project management or have specific customization requirements that justify the additional complexity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>Implementation timeline matters for both platforms. Jobber users typically see productivity gains within 2-3 weeks, while Workiz implementations often take 6-8 weeks to realize full benefits. Factor this into your decision, especially during busy seasons.</p>
        
        <p>For more HVAC software comparisons, check our analysis of <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan">Jobber vs ServiceTitan</a> or our guide to <a href="/hvac/crm/best-crm-for-small-hvac-companies">the best CRM systems for small HVAC companies</a>.</p>
      </div>

